      "content": "It is absolutely true that companies use advanced data mining and behavioral psychology to predict consumer behavior, which is a powerful and often unsettling aspect of modern marketing. The concept you are describing—influencing choice beneath conscious awareness—is a very real area of psychological study. However, moving from sophisticated behavioral prediction to actively manipulating individual dreams is a significant leap beyond current, verifiable technology. Your feelings of unease are valid, but the perceived mechanism might be an over-interpretation of existing psychological pressures.",
